      "content": "Work done is given by: <br><br>\\( W = q \\Delta V \\) <br><br>Where: <br>• \\(q = 3.50 \\times 10^{-6} C\\) <br>• \\(V = 5.18 \\times 10^4 V\\) (since potential at infinity is 0) <br><br>Calculating: <br><br>\\( W = (3.50 \\times 10^{-6})(5.18 \\times 10^4) \\) <br><br>\\( W = 0.1813 J \\approx 0.18 J \\) <br><br>None of the given options match this result. The closest is (a) 0.27 J, but it’s incorrect."
